properties.areaDesc: Port Washington to North Point Light WI; Sheboygan to Port Washington WI; Wind Point WI to Winthrop Harbor IL; North Point Light to Wind Point WI
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 9 at 3:28PM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, southwest winds 15 to 25
kt with gusts up to 30 kt and waves 5 to 8 feet. For the Gale
Watch, northeast winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 45 kt and
waves 8 to 13 feet possible.

* WHERE...Sheboygan to Port Washington WI, Port Washington to
North Point Light WI, North Point Light to Wind Point WI and
Wind Point WI to Winthrop Harbor IL.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 3 AM CST Friday.
For the Gale Watch, from late Friday night through late
Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.
